subject: Swimming
Deaths (Fatalities)
Olympic Games (2012)
lead_paragraph: Alexander Dale Oen of Norway, the reigning world champion in the 100-meter breaststroke, died of cardiac arrest while in Flagstaff, Ariz., training with the Norwegian national team. He was 26.
